1
00:00:07,220 --> 00:00:11,820
♪She looks at the bright moon
hanging high above the clouds♪

2
00:00:11,860 --> 00:00:14,140
♪And I fall into the mountains♪

3
00:00:14,220 --> 00:00:16,100
♪Protect this broken world♪

4
00:00:16,180 --> 00:00:20,620
♪A faint wish♪

5
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:23,900
♪Life is just a dream,
isn't the world so?♪

6
00:00:23,980 --> 00:00:27,620
♪Looking back,
I count the joys of my remaining years♪

7
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:31,020
♪It's difficult to see you in my dreams♪

8
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:33,940
♪Ignoring the coldness of the world,
I still linger♪

9
00:00:33,980 --> 00:00:37,300
♪Love and hate are intertwined,
not just in the past♪

10
00:00:37,340 --> 00:00:40,900
♪The past is painful,
and time goes by in a flash♪

11
00:00:40,940 --> 00:00:44,500
♪Stars fall on the mountain top again♪

12
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:48,140
♪My heart is as pure as the moon
and connected to you♪

13
00:00:54,140 --> 00:00:56,980
[No One But You]

14
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:57,700
[Episode 9]

15
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:01,980
[We gaze at each other across the crowd,
unable to advance or retreat.]

16
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,750
[Joys of Life]

17
00:01:24,580 --> 00:01:25,460
Today,

18
00:01:25,580 --> 00:01:26,780
in Beizhou,

19
00:01:27,140 --> 00:01:29,980
I'm honored to have
all the prominent figures here.

20
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:32,860
Thank you for coming.

21
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,460
The only thing you would expect
from following me

22
00:01:37,460 --> 00:01:39,940
is to earn money

23
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:42,860
and enjoy our lives together.

24
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:43,980
Cheers!

25
00:01:57,540 --> 00:01:58,660
What are you doing here?

26
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:01,860
The Marshal specially invited me.

27
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:03,380
What,

28
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:05,460
do you have a problem?

29
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:09,220
It seems tonight,

30
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:12,140
I'll have to treat you well.

31
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,300
I'm looking forward to it.

32
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,820
Everyone, please look behind.

33
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:58,020
The highlight of today's ball is

34
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,380
bidding

35
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:03,500
for a dance with Miss Yu.

36
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:04,500
The highest bidder wins.

37
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,420
Wait.

38
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:08,460
Since the Marshal has requested,

39
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:10,220
I shouldn't have declined.

40
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:11,500
But I, Yu Qinghuan,

41
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:13,540
don't want to be a commodity.

42
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:15,940
I don't care about
how much money you bid.

43
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:18,700
Not even it's your request, Marshal.

44
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:24,620
But I'll agree to the auction.

45
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:26,700
I'm willing to donate all the money

46
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:28,500
to Beizhou Charity Orphanage.

47
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:33,060
Miss Yu is truly a kind-hearted person.

48
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,900
The auction starts now.

49
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:41,900
I bid 500 silver coins.

50
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:43,500
I bid 600 silver coins.

51
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,620
I bid 700 silver coins.

52
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:45,660
I bid 800 silver coins.

53
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:46,260
A thousand.

54
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,060
Ten bars of gold.

55
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:51,020
That's a lot.

56
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:53,020
Twenty.

57
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:57,780
Fifty.

58
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:58,820
One hundred.

59
00:04:05,380 --> 00:04:06,900
Are you going head-to-head with me?

60
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,340
The highest bidder wins.

61
00:04:08,860 --> 00:04:10,540
Please continue, Mr. Chu.

62
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:13,380
If we take turns competing,

63
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,620
there will never be a winner.

64
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:21,500
That's not necessarily true.

65
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:24,100
It depends on who's better.

66
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,460
Jiang, Chu,

67
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:27,820
do me a favor, please.

68
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:30,420
Please don't make it look bad.

69
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:33,740
Let's change the game.

70
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:38,860
The winner can donate 100 bars of gold

71
00:04:38,860 --> 00:04:41,580
and dance with Miss Yu, okay?

72
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:44,100
Sure.

73
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:46,860
Let's do something less boring.

74
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:48,380
That's what I'm thinking.

75
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:53,340
What about Russian roulette?

76
00:05:01,820 --> 00:05:02,940
A bullet

77
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:04,220
will determine your life.

78
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:05,700
Whoever wants to stop

79
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,500
can quit in any round.

80
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,660
Who wants to go first?

81
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:47,060
Mohan,

82
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:48,380
the probability of this round

83
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:50,260
is increased to one-fourth.

84
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,340
Are you worrying about me?

85
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:07,980
The probability of getting shot

86
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:09,620
is now one-third.

87
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,820
Do you want to continue?

88
00:06:11,060 --> 00:06:12,060
Of course.

89
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,780
Thankfully, Lady Luck
smiled on me today.

90
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,380
Mohan,

91
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:37,100
now it's an either-or.

92
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:48,340
What,

93
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:50,260
are you afraid?

94
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:50,860
No.

95
00:06:52,860 --> 00:06:54,820
I'm putting my life in your hands.

96
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:57,060
You're going to shoot me.

97
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:28,220
Your life

98
00:07:28,460 --> 00:07:29,860
is not easy to take.

99
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,300
Chu Yunfan.

100
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:40,020
Jiang Mohan.

101
00:07:40,420 --> 00:07:42,260
You truly are heroes

102
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:43,380
in this close game.

103
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:44,340
All right,

104
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:46,260
the game is over.

105
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:47,660
Miss Yu,

106
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,340
please choose by yourself.

107
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:52,980
Then I'll choose

108
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:55,940
Mr. Chu.

109
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,900
It's so worth it

110
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,580
gambling with my life.

111
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,620
The bullet was specially made.

112
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:35,900
It won't kill anyone.

113
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:37,500
It will only make a fool
out of the person.

114
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:38,660
It's a shame.

115
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:53,540
Jiang.

116
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:01,740
This is the daughter of the president
of the Japanese Chamber of Commerce

117
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:03,460
that I mentioned to you.

118
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:04,540
Miss Chihoko.

119
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:09,780
Miss Chihoko.

120
00:09:11,380 --> 00:09:13,380
I've heard a lot about you, Mr. Jiang.

121
00:09:13,380 --> 00:09:14,540
Pleased to meet you.

122
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,900
May I have a dance with you?

123
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:21,580
Of course.

124
00:09:21,860 --> 00:09:22,660
Here.

125
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:49,140
You look

126
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:51,180
a bit different from other Chinese men

127
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:52,140
that I've met.

128
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:54,260
Oh, is that so?

129
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:58,620
You're the man
who calls the shot in this era.

130
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:02,020
Of course,
you're unlike any ordinary man.

131
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:05,460
Even the Marshal is no match for you.

132
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:08,300
Please watch what you say, Miss Chihoko.

133
00:10:23,220 --> 00:10:24,740
I'm sorry

134
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:26,500
to spoil your fun, Mohan.

135
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:40,820
Now it's time
for questions from the press.

136
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:43,060
We will answer every question

137
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,300
as long as we can.

138
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,460
Military Governor, you've been searching
for members of the Sparks Society,

139
00:10:46,460 --> 00:10:47,420
going so far as to kill the innocent,

140
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:48,820
causing panic among the public.

141
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,300
Would you have an explanation?

142
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:52,300
You're asking me for an explanation?

143
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:08,420
[Jiang Mohan the hideous murderer]

144
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:27,460
[The lonely boat
sailing through troubled waters]

145
00:11:36,260 --> 00:11:37,740
All the celebrities in the city
will be here.

146
00:11:38,420 --> 00:11:40,180
I hope Guzhou sees the message

147
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:41,340
and contacts me.

148
00:12:02,370 --> 00:12:08,920
[The willow shore
is hoping for your return]

149
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,070
[Joys of Life]

150
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:55,900
♪The waves♪

151
00:12:55,980 --> 00:13:00,180
♪When will you stop
looking through them?♪

152
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:04,220
♪Missed the time
when the sun was restored♪

153
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:08,380
♪What else do you expect to like?♪

154
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:11,140
♪I thought you were an angel♪

155
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:13,420
♪An angel who watched over me♪

156
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:16,500
♪And saw every side of me♪

157
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:19,140
♪Until reality is flooded♪

158
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:21,380
♪You become sensible♪

159
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:25,940
♪You are finally
out of touch with reality♪

160
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:28,780
♪I hear the mountains, the seas,
and the people♪

161
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:30,820
♪All clamoring because of you♪

162
00:13:30,940 --> 00:13:32,900
♪Hiding in the cape after the rain♪

163
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:35,340
♪I cannot hear you♪

164
00:13:35,380 --> 00:13:38,860
♪So I opened my arms one last time♪

165
00:13:39,020 --> 00:13:42,380
♪But you escaped through the gap♪

166
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:44,700
♪I saw winters come and summers go♪

167
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,860
♪And thought there was ample time♪

168
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:48,900
♪Cannot withstand the waves♪

169
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:50,980
♪But you always make me panic♪

170
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:55,300
♪How ridiculous, making me learn♪

171
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:58,660
♪How much I am worth♪
